headline: Alphabet Earnings: Is AI Killing Google Search?
summary: A: Google’s ubiquitous search tool has proved surprisingly resilient to competition from the likes of OpenAI, which is hoping people will skip the search box and ask its chatbot for answers instead.  One of Google’s lines of defense has been its “AI Overview” tool, where users can see answers generated by its Gemini AI model hovering above their traditional search results.  Google is also rolling out an “AI Mode” that competes more directly with chatbots.

headline: Bright spots emerge in corporate earnings as tariff uncertainty lingers
summary: Corporate operations have been overshadowed by erratic U.S. trade action that has upended supply chains and left firms to navigate fluid tariffs on top of broader economic uncertainties such as regulatory change and currency fluctuation. Nvidia supplier SK Hynix booked record quarterly profit, boosted by strong demand for artificial intelligence chips and customers stockpiling ahead of potential U.S. tariffs.
